---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
---

<Layout title="Resources & The DeFlock Movement">
  <div class="content">
    <span class="card-tag" style="background: rgba(42, 157, 143, 0.2); color: #2A9D8F;">Resources</span>
    <h1>You're Not Alone In This</h1>
    <p class="subtitle" style="color: var(--color-muted); font-size: 1.15rem;">
      DeFlock Safford is the local node of a national movement that already has maps, model legislation, audits, and organizers. We don't reinvent any of it. We point you to it and add the Graham County piece.
    </p>

    <h2>See the Cameras Near You</h2>
    <p>
      The <strong>DeFlock</strong> project crowdsources ALPR camera locations onto OpenStreetMap, the largest open surveillance registry, with 336,000+ cameras logged nationwide. As of our last check, the community has mapped <strong>at least 45 ALPR cameras in Graham County</strong> (44 tagged Flock Safety, 1 Motorola), with about 35 clustered in the Safford/Thatcher core. That's a floor, not a ceiling, crowdsourced maps undercount.
    </p>
    <a href="https://deflock.me" class="card" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
      <h3>DeFlock.me &amp; maps.deflock.org &rarr;</h3>
      <p>Interactive national camera map. Allow location to center on Safford. Free, no account. You can also report cameras you spot to add them to the map.</p>
    </a>

    <h2>Find Out If Your Agency Has a Contract</h2>
    <a href="https://www.aclu.org/get-the-flock-out-toolkit" class="card" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
      <h3>ACLU &mdash; "Get the Flock Out" Toolkit &rarr;</h3>
      <p>The national playbook: model bills to cancel or restrict ALPR contracts, a directory of local organizing groups, and step-by-step guidance. This is the resource to bring to a city council fight.</p>
    </a>
    <a href="https://eyesonflock.com" class="card" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
      <h3>Have I Been Flocked? / Eyes on Flock &rarr;</h3>
      <p>Crowdsourced lists of public audits and Flock transparency portals. Search whether your local agency has a contract and what its audit shows.</p>
    </a>
    <a href="https://alprwatch.org" class="card" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
      <h3>ALPR Watch &rarr;</h3>
      <p>Tracks confirmed and suspected ALPR installations (the latter from utility-permit data), with an API and offline data packages.</p>
    </a>

    <h2>Local Chapters That Did This Already</h2>
    <p>
      These are the model for what DeFlock Safford is. Small communities that organized, brought receipts, and moved their councils.
    </p>
    <a href="https://deflocktucson.com" class="card" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
      <h3>DeFlock Tucson &rarr;</h3>
      <p>The Arizona chapter closest to us. Helped push South Tucson to cancel its Flock contract in February 2026. Same state, same network, same fight.</p>
    </a>
    <a href="https://www.maryvilleprivacy.org" class="card" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
      <h3>Maryville Residents for Privacy (TN) &rarr;</h3>
      <p>A small-town template worth copying: a local camera map, a council accountability report, and a sample community letter. Proof this works outside big cities.</p>
    </a>

    <h2>The Receipts We Cite</h2>
    <p>
      Every claim on this site traces to one of these. We list them so you can check our work, and use them in your own.
    </p>
    <div class="card">
      <ul class="card-specifics">
        <li><strong>Electronic Frontier Foundation</strong> &mdash; the protest-tracking investigation, Nova analysis, and Flock litigation (eff.org)</li>
        <li><strong>ACLU</strong> &mdash; Flock expansion reporting, the Palantir deportation roundup, and NSPM-7 analysis (aclu.org)</li>
        <li><strong>OHCHR / UN</strong> &mdash; the Special Rapporteur's "Economy of Genocide" report naming Palantir (ohchr.org)</li>
        <li><strong>404 Media, Fortune, TIME, SF Standard</strong> &mdash; the original investigative reporting</li>
        <li><strong>Arizona outlets</strong> &mdash; AZPM, Tucson Spotlight, KGUN9, KOLD, Phoenix New Times for the in-state record</li>
        <li><strong>OpenStreetMap</strong> &mdash; the Graham County camera data, via the Overpass API (surveillance:type=ALPR)</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="cta-banner">
      <h3>Now Do the Local Part</h3>
      <p>The national tools exist. The Graham County records request and petition are the piece only we can do.</p>
      <a href={`${base}records/`} class="btn">Records Request</a>
      <a href={`${base}petition/`} class="btn btn-outline">Sign the Petition</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
